  "title": "Pest Control Technician",
  "description": "<p>We are hiring a Pest Control Technician to join our team. As a Pest Control Technician, you will be responsible for inspecting properties, identifying pest infestations, and implementing effective pest control measures. Your role will involve treating infested areas, educating clients on prevention methods, and maintaining accurate records of services provided.</p><ul><li>Perform through inspections of properties to identify pest infections</li><li>Apply appropriate pest control methods, including the use of chemicals and traps</li><li>Safely handle and apple pesticides according to established procedures</li><li>Educate clients on effective pest prevention techniques and sanitation practices</li><li>Document all services provided and maintain accurate records</li><li>Respons promptly and professionally to client inquiries, concerns, and industry developments</li><li>Adhere to company policies, industry regulations, and ethical practices</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>5 or 5.5 days work per week</li><li>Preferred 1 year of experience working as a pest control technician / worker</li><li>Valid NEA Vector Control Technician License or Vector Control worker</li></ul>",
